'''Heikki Kirkinen''' (22 September 1927 in [[Kuusj√§rvi]] ‚Äì 9 January 2018) was a Finnish historian who was professor of [[Finnish history|Finnish]] and [[European history]] at the [[University of Eastern Finland]] in [[Joensuu]], [[Finland]]. He has been a visiting professor in the Finnish language, literature and culture at [[Sorbonne]], 1966‚Äì1970.
Kirkinen has written many books about the [[Karelia]]n history and the Karelian identity. One of his main interests was music; he has studied musicology and even composed music himself.
